cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper belongs to the field of computer security (cs.CR) as it focuses on cybercrime forums and supply chains. The proposed method for automatically extracting supply chains involves the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.AI) and natural language processing techniques (cs.IR). The paper also involves data analysis and pattern recognition (cs.LG) to identify underlying connections between products and services within the forums. Finally, the paper's emphasis on understanding and intervention in criminal activities suggests a potential overlap with social impact (cs.SI) sub-category.
